Howto Rasta on Mac OS X
-----------------------

 First of all Xcode (latest version for compiling sources)

1. **Python**:

 Python already installed in OSX (to test it open Terminal and type “python”)

2. **Qt4**:

 http://qt.nokia.com/downloads/sdk-mac-os-cpp (DMG: install as usual)

3. **SIP**:

 http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/software/sip/download

 You can use sip-snapshot*.zip/tar.gz (development snapshot)

 Installing::
  
  python configure.py
  make
  sudo make install
  cd ..

4. **PyQT**:

 http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/software/pyqt/download

 You can use PyQt*snapshot*.zip/tar.gz (development snapshot)

 Installing::
  
  python configure.py
  make
  sudo make install
  cd ..

5. **QScintilla**:

 http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/software/qscintilla/download

 You can use QScintilla-gpl*.zip/tar.gz (development snapshot)

 Installing::

  cd QScintilla*
  cd Qt4
  qmake qscintilla.pro -spec macx-g++
  make
  sudo make install

 Qsci module::

  cd ../Python
  python configure.py
  make
  sudo make install

6. **Docutils**:

 http://prdownloads.sourceforge.net/docutils/docutils-0.6.tar.gz?download

 Installing::

  cd docutils-0.6
  sudo python setup.py install

7. **Piksemel**:

 http://svn.pardus.org.tr/uludag/trunk/piksemel

 You can check-out it by::

  $ svn co http://svn.pardus.org.tr/uludag/trunk/piksemel

 Installing::

  cd piksemel
  sudo python setup.py install

8. **Rasta \\o/**:

 http://svn.pardus.org.tr/uludag/trunk/rasta

 You can check-out it by::

  $ svn co http://svn.pardus.org.tr/uludag/trunk/rasta

 Installing::

  cd rasta
  sudo python setup.py install

And you can run it by calling::

 $ rasta

*References for PyQt on Mac OS X from* http://www.bdigit.com/blog/2010/02/python-qt4-sip-qscintilla-eric4-tutorial-mac-os-x/
